text: Muztagh Tower is a mountain in the Karakoram range, in China and Pakistan. It is part of the Baltoro Muztagh subrange. Muztagh Tower is the 90th highest mountain in the world. The first people to reach the top were Ian McNaught- Davis, Joe Brown, John Hartog, and Tom Patey, in 1956. == References == Category:Mountains of Xinjiang Category:Mountains of Gilgit-Baltistan Category:Karakoram
